        },
        {
            "title": "Cultural and Architectural Heritage of Milan",
            "content": "Milan is renowned for its rich cultural and architectural heritage, which reflects its historical significance and modern dynamism. The city's skyline is a blend of historic and contemporary architecture, symbolizing its ability to preserve tradition while embracing innovation. The Duomo di Milano, a masterpiece of Gothic architecture, is one of the largest cathedrals in the world and a symbol of the city. Another architectural marvel is the Galleria Vittorio Emanuele II, one of the world's oldest shopping malls, known for its stunning glass and iron architecture. Milan's cultural scene is vibrant, with numerous museums, theaters, and galleries. The La Scala opera house is one of the most prestigious opera venues globally, attracting world-class performers. The city's art scene is equally impressive, with institutions like the Pinacoteca di Brera and the Museo del Novecento showcasing works from the Renaissance to contemporary art. Milan's cultural calendar is packed with events, from the Milan Fashion Week to the Salone del Mobile, reflecting its status as a global design capital. The city's diverse cultural offerings and architectural landmarks make it a must-visit destination for art and history enthusiasts.",
            "relevance_score": 0.88
        }
    ]
}
